text: Paricutin is a volcano in Mexico in the state of Michoacán. It is the youngest volcano in the western hemisphere, born in 1943.Parucutin at 7 wonders*Parícutin at Peakbagger.com It is now 1,353 feet (424m) above the valley, and 9,186 feet (2,800m) above sea level. == References == Category:Volcanoes of Mexico
title: Parícutin
